  "prompt": "What can I do with an infant at Walt Disney World?",
  "response": "Here are some infant-friendly activities and tips for Walt Disney World:\n\n1. Attractions suitable for infants:\n- Many slow, gentle rides like \"It's a Small World\"\n- The Carousel\n- Tram rides\n- People mover\n- Trains\n\n2. Baby Care Centers:\n- Located in each park\n- Offer:\n- Changing tables\n- Private nursing areas\n- High chairs\n- Microwaves\n- Infant supplies for purchase\n\n3. Stroller considerations:\n- Bring your own or rent from Disney\n- Free stroller parking at attractions\n- Comfortable for naps and breaks\n\n4. Practical tips:\n- Use baby carrier/wrap\n- Bring sun protection\n- Pack extra diapers, wipes\n- Bring portable fan\n- Schedule breaks\n- Consider short park visits\n\n5. Recommended parks for infants:\n- Magic Kingdom (most kid-friendly)\n- EPCOT (lots of shaded areas)\n\n6. Age-appropriate meets:\n- Character meet-and-greets\n- Many characters are gentle with babies\n- Good photo opportunities\n\n7. Dining:\n- Many restaurants have high chairs\n- Quiet areas for feeding\n- Kid-friendly menu options\n\nRemember to go at your baby's pace and be flexible.",
